That should work, but there&#39;s an even simpler way, starting from the 
default set of DecideRules.

Set the TooManyHopsDecideRule&#39;s maxHops value to 0. Then, *every* 
discovered outlink (both &#39;embeds&#39; like IMG+CSS+JS and &#39;navlinks&#39; like 
A/HREF) will get a REJECT from that rule... because everything but the 
seeds themselves will have a &#39;hops count&#39; of 1 or higher.

However, since the default configuration still has the 
TransclusionDecideRule later, it will &#39;rescue&#39; some of the outlinks -- 
the &#39;embeds&#39; that you want -- by changing the scoping-decision to ACCEPT 
when the last hop (or several) are all &#39;transcluded&#39; types.

That rule&#39;s other parameters, maxTransHops (all E+R+X type hops) and 
maxSpeculativeHops (just X hops) can further tune how much such 
&#39;transclusion&#39; of referenced-but-not-necessarily-navigational outlinks 
should be followed.

- Gordon

On 10/9/13 10:29 AM, Kristinn Sigur�sson wrote:
&gt; Hi Zsolt,
&gt;
&gt; The simplest way to do this is to add a HopsPathMatchesRegexDecideRule to your scope. Set the rule to REJECT matches and configure the regular expression as &quot;.*L.*&quot;. This will reject any URLs whose hop paths include an L hop (i.e. link) while allowing embeds, redirects and preconditions to be fetched.
&gt;
&gt; The below is untested but should work:
&gt;
&gt;          &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.HopsPathMatchesRegexDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;                  &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot; /&gt;
&gt;                  &lt;property name=&quot;regex&quot; value=&quot;.*L.*&quot; /&gt;
&gt;          &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Just insert it into the scope immediately prior to the preconditions rule.
&gt;
&gt; - Kris
